  "title": "BIM Modeller (Lead) - Consultancy Firm",
  "description": "<h3><strong>Responsibilities</strong></h3>\n<ul>\n  <li>Develop and maintain an effective framework for drawing and BIM model production.</li>\n  <li>Prepare detailed CAD drawings and BIM models that meet project specifications.</li>\n  <li>Lead and guide junior designers in producing high-quality drawings and BIM deliverables.</li>\n  <li>Coordinate closely with engineers and provide regular updates on project progress.</li>\n  <li>Ensure proper management and organization of CAD/BIM files in accordance with workflow standards.</li>\n  <li>Perform any other related duties as assigned.</li>\n</ul>\n<h3><strong>Requirements</strong></h3>\n<ul>\n  <li>Diploma or ITE qualification in Civil, Structural, or a related engineering discipline from a recognized institution.</li>\n  <li>At least 6 years of relevant experience in civil or structural design within an engineering consultancy preferred.</li>\n  <li>BIM certification or diploma will be an advantage.</li>\n  <li>Experience in BIM production within a contractor environment will be highly regarded.</li>\n</ul>\n<p><br></p>\n<p>Interested candidates who wish to apply for the advertised position, please click on the APPLY button below to send in your resume.</p>\n<p><br></p>\n<p>EA License No: 13C6305</p>\n<p><br></p>\n<p>Reg. No.: R22104949 KOH SHI MIN, JOAN (XU SHIMIN)</p>\n<p><br></p>\n<p>For candidates who applied for the advertised position is deemed to have consented to us that we may collect, use or disclose your personal information for purpose in connection with the services provided by us.</p>",
